Data Center Overview:
Holds physical or virtual servers.
Server Functionality:
Runs the operating system and programs.
Web Server:
Serves webpages in static or dynamic form.
Database:
Stores application data, fetched from the codebase upon request.
DNS (Domain Name System):
Maps domain names (e.g., www.foobar.com) to IP addresses (e.g., 8.8.8.8) using A records.
Communication Protocol:
Transmission Control Protocol/Internet Protocol (TCP/IP) used for communication.
Single Point of Failure (SPOF):
Server serves as a single point of failure, lacking redundancy.
Issues:
Inability to handle traffic exceeding server capacity.
Requires restarting when new code is sent, causing downtime.

